verdict: |
  Phase B is the right work and vision-coherent. Packaging is the problem: Phases A/C/D/E inflate scope with DX work
  unrelated to the convergence-testing vision, attribution posture undermines positioning, vocabulary collisions
  with existing Loom concepts are unresolved, and a critical UX dead-end exists in the Phase B gate itself.
  Recommended next: refine F-18 to address blocking findings before /loom-plan create.
